Galy et al. [46] performed high precision magnesium isotope ratio measurements using MC-ICP-MS for three groups of materials: commercial Mg materials including the NIST isotopic standard SRM 980, natural magnesite, and commercial chlorophyll in spinach. The observed ratio 26Mg/24Mg was 0.139828 ± 0.000037 (2σ), compared to the NIST value of 0.13932 ± 0.000 6 (2σ) [47]. The variations in the Mg materials reported in δ25Mg and δ26Mg units are given in Table 2. A desolvation nebulizer was used to minimize the introduction of H2O, CO2, O2, and N2, therefore reducing the presence in the plasma of molecular interferences such as \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
